Private-equity firm GI Partners LLC
may acquire all or part of University Partnerships Programme, a
developer of university campuses owned by the infrastructure
funds of  Barclays Capital , the Sunday Times reported.  Barclays Capital has asked  UBS AG (UBS)  to start a process that
may result in the sale of all or part of UPP, the newspaper
reported, without saying where it got the information. UPP may
be worth more than 1 billion pounds ($1.64 billion), the London-
based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
